reviews.text: So I‚Äôve been coming here for years, ordering a small pizza - individual size. I live basically down the street from this place and have met the owner Don several times. I  usually ordered the personal or individual size but today I decide to upgrade to a medium and use their new app. I was so disappointed with my pizza which was terrible that I decided to call to see if maybe the place was under new management as I said I never had a bad pizza prior. The pizza I had was so bad I had to throw it out! The outer third of the pizza edges of it were burnt and the pepperoni was dry and crispy and it was very very thin. The toppings were also very poor on it. I spoke to somebody who identified himself as a manager, and when I started complaining about the pizza he Became very defensive - saying he made the pizza himself and that the way he made it is perfect and that other customers who ordered the exact same pizza as mine that moment (had to believe there would be : other customers who ordered the exact same pizza at the same time) had no complaints and then proceeded to hang up the phone on me. What a poor business model to have this manager in place dealing with customers, he needs definite training on how to handle the public. I will not be back! In addition just know that if you order a pizza from here you may have him making it.

Stopped there on 7/25/25 and ordered a large two topping pizza; half with pepperoni and sausage, the other half had pepperoni and green peppers.

This was our first time here. The order was made quickly, and let me tell you how goooood their pizza is!!!! Reminds me of Lu's in Grafton, just with a thicker crust (that I prefer). I would most definitely order from there again, and plan to do so.

Excellent service too! Y'all are doing everything right!!!
Finally got around to trying the pizza here. I was pleased with both pizzas. I got the New York crust and there was no flop! I'll be back for sure!

Wow, first time for their pizza, and it was Really Really good.  The crust, sauce, cheese, all perfect.   Big menu of interesting items, but started simple with a personal pepperoni and onion pizza.   Highly recommend and will be back soon. Sure wish they had a dining room.

Son and I were in town for a sports function and decided to give 'A Slice Above' a try. For starters, the man who answered the phone was very nice. I ordered a large plain cheese and fries. Food was ready for pickup when he told us and I also grabbed some soft drinks from their cooler. Everyone inside was fantastic. Very friendly staff.

Brought the food back to the hotel and my son and I absolutely demolished the pizza and fries. Pizza was delicious! Had a wonderful flavor and the crust was perfect. Fries were very good as well, above standard pizza shop fries.

I highly recommend 'A Slice Above' as we will certainly order again when in the area!

I like most everyone have gotten sick of just eating pizza but A Slice Above still rates the highest in my book and I continue to order from them because my favorite Buffalo chicken ranch I don't think I could really ever get that tired of it. It is just ONE of the unique pizzas they offer. The Popeye pie is to die for, you'll love it.

The variety and uniqueness of pizza options, such as the Jimmy Hoffa and Body Builder pizzas, are highly appreciated by customers. - social media marketing can showcase this strength
